{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-19",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_19_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 19 - The Russian's Hand",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 7,
  "page_total": 10,
  "page_start_sec": 1471.04,
  "page_end_sec": 1714.16,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.671,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 1471.04,
      "end": 1472.24,
      "text": "I ought to have more than ten",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1472.32,
      "end": 1472.896,
      "text": "thousand.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1474.112,
      "end": 1474.64,
      "text": "Gutman said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1475.424,
      "end": 1477.6,
      "text": "\"'Ten thousand dollars is a lot of money.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1478.4,
      "end": 1479.04,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1479.98,
      "end": 1480.72,
      "text": "\"'You're quoting me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1480.84,
      "end": 1482.88,
      "text": "but it's not all the money in the world.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1483.42,
      "end": 1483.96,
      "text": "\"'No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1483.96,
      "end": 1484.14,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1484.24,
      "end": 1484.8,
      "text": "it's not."
    },
    {
      "start": 1484.96,
      "end": 1486.16,
      "text": "I grant you that."
    },
    {
      "start": 1486.96,
      "end": 1488.44,
      "text": "But it's a lot of money to be",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1488.62,
      "end": 1491.84,
      "text": "picked up in as few days and as easily as you're getting it.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1492.52,
      "end": 1496.66,
      "text": "\"'You think it's been so damned easy?' Spade asked and shrugged.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1497.32,
      "end": 1497.58,
      "text": "\"'Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1497.58,
      "end": 1497.88,
      "text": "maybe,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1498.08,
      "end": 1499.4,
      "text": "but that's my business.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1500.256,
      "end": 1502.64,
      "text": "\"'It certainly is,' the fat man agreed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1503.4,
      "end": 1505.0,
      "text": "He screwed up his eyes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1505.16,
      "end": 1506.82,
      "text": "moved his head to indicate the kitchen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1506.92,
      "end": 1507.98,
      "text": "and lowered his voice."
    },
    {
      "start": 1509.7,
      "end": 1511.19,
      "text": "\"'Are you sharing with her?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1512.16,
      "end": 1512.74,
      "text": "Spade said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1513.664,
      "end": 1514.4,
      "text": "\"'That's my business,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1514.54,
      "end": 1515.04,
      "text": "too.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1515.776,
      "end": 1518.86,
      "text": "\"'It certainly is,' the fat man agreed once more.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1519.7,
      "end": 1520.16,
      "text": "\"'But—'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1520.96,
      "end": 1521.54,
      "text": "he hesitated.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1522.52,
      "end": 1524.38,
      "text": "I'd like to give you a word of advice.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1525.5,
      "end": 1526.26,
      "text": "\"'Go ahead.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1527.872,
      "end": 1528.74,
      "text": "\"'If you don't,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1529.2,
      "end": 1529.84,
      "text": "I dare say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1530.02,
      "end": 1532.1,
      "text": "you'll give her some money in any event,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1532.54,
      "end": 1535.64,
      "text": "but if you don't give her as much as she thinks you ought to have,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1536.14,
      "end": 1537.52,
      "text": "my word of advice is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1537.62,
      "end": 1538.944,
      "text": "be careful.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1539.968,
      "end": 1541.7,
      "text": "Spade's eyes held a mocking light.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1542.16,
      "end": 1542.7,
      "text": "He asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1543.18,
      "end": 1543.94,
      "text": "\"'Bad?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1544.48,
      "end": 1546.6,
      "text": "\"'Bad,' the fat man replied."
    },
    {
      "start": 1548.032,
      "end": 1550.02,
      "text": "Spade grinned and began to roll the cigarette.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1550.89,
      "end": 1551.54,
      "text": "Cairo,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1551.78,
      "end": 1553.32,
      "text": "still muttering in the boy's ear,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1553.9,
      "end": 1555.72,
      "text": "had put his arm around his shoulders again."
    },
    {
      "start": 1556.928,
      "end": 1558.94,
      "text": "Suddenly the boy pushed his arm away and",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1558.94,
      "end": 1561.32,
      "text": "twisted around on the sofa to face Cairo."
    },
    {
      "start": 1562.34,
      "end": 1564.66,
      "text": "The boy's face held anger and disgust.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1565.6,
      "end": 1567.98,
      "text": "He made a fist of a small hand and struck the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1568.06,
      "end": 1569.16,
      "text": "Levantine's mouth with it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1570.144,
      "end": 1573.22,
      "text": "Cairo cried out as a woman might have cried and drew back to the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1573.22,
      "end": 1574.24,
      "text": "very end of the sofa."
    },
    {
      "start": 1575.02,
      "end": 1578.34,
      "text": "He took a silk handkerchief from his pocket and put it to his mouth.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1578.66,
      "end": 1580.64,
      "text": "It came away daubed with blood."
    },
    {
      "start": 1580.98,
      "end": 1584.52,
      "text": "He put it to his mouth again and looked reproachfully at the boy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1585.24,
      "end": 1586.08,
      "text": "The boy snarled,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1586.64,
      "end": 1587.86,
      "text": "Keep away from me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1588.42,
      "end": 1590.22,
      "text": "and put his face between his hands again."
    },
    {
      "start": 1591.296,
      "end": 1594.36,
      "text": "Cairo's handkerchief released the fragrance of sheepra in the room.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1595.648,
      "end": 1598.4,
      "text": "Cairo's cry had drawn Bridget O'Shaughnessy to the door.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1599.25,
      "end": 1599.8,
      "text": "Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1599.82,
      "end": 1600.22,
      "text": "grinning,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1600.26,
      "end": 1602.2,
      "text": "jerked a thumb at the sofa and told her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1603.06,
      "end": 1604.3,
      "text": "The course of true love.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1604.85,
      "end": 1606.16,
      "text": "How's the food coming along?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1607.6,
      "end": 1608.84,
      "text": "\"'It's coming,' she said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1608.94,
      "end": 1610.0,
      "text": "and returned to the kitchen."
    },
    {
      "start": 1611.232,
      "end": 1613.56,
      "text": "Spade lighted his cigarette and addressed Gutman.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1614.848,
      "end": 1616.064,
      "text": "\"'Let's talk about the money.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1616.62,
      "end": 1617.2,
      "text": "\"'Willingly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1617.2,
      "end": 1617.48,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1617.58,
      "end": 1620.12,
      "text": "with all my heart,' the fat man replied."
    },
    {
      "start": 1620.96,
      "end": 1623.34,
      "text": "\"'But I might as well tell you frankly right now",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1623.34,
      "end": 1626.47,
      "text": "that ten thousand is every cent I can raise.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1627.552,
      "end": 1628.9,
      "text": "Spade exhaled the smoke.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1630.02,
      "end": 1630.8,
      "text": "\"'I ought to have twenty.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1631.66,
      "end": 1632.5,
      "text": "I wish you could.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1633.152,
      "end": 1634.16,
      "text": "I'd give it to you gladly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1634.36,
      "end": 1635.46,
      "text": "if I had it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1635.58,
      "end": 1639.648,
      "text": "but ten thousand is every cent I can manage on my word of honor.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1640.9,
      "end": 1641.24,
      "text": "\"'All right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1641.24,
      "end": 1641.48,
      "text": "then."
    },
    {
      "start": 1641.58,
      "end": 1643.12,
      "text": "Call it fifteen thousand.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1644.32,
      "end": 1646.52,
      "text": "Gutman smiled and frowned and shook his head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1647.29,
      "end": 1647.94,
      "text": "\"'Mr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1648.14,
      "end": 1648.54,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1648.74,
      "end": 1651.12,
      "text": "I've told you frankly and candidly"
    },
    {
      "start": 1651.12,
      "end": 1653.1,
      "text": "and on my word of honor as a gentleman"
    },
    {
      "start": 1653.7,
      "end": 1656.42,
      "text": "that ten thousand dollars is all the money I've got,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1656.56,
      "end": 1657.88,
      "text": "all I can raise.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1658.82,
      "end": 1659.32,
      "text": "\"'Sure,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1659.36,
      "end": 1660.14,
      "text": "you told me that."
    },
    {
      "start": 1660.98,
      "end": 1662.01,
      "text": "But you didn't say positively.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1663.648,
      "end": 1664.62,
      "text": "Gutman laughed and said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1665.14,
      "end": 1666.08,
      "text": "Positively."
    },
    {
      "start": 1667.232,
      "end": 1668.36,
      "text": "Spade said gloomily,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1669.472,
      "end": 1670.58,
      "text": "That's not any too good,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1671.02,
      "end": 1672.2,
      "text": "but if it's the best you can do,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1672.32,
      "end": 1673.06,
      "text": "give it to me."
    },
    {
      "start": 1674.304,
      "end": 1675.52,
      "text": "Gutman handed him the envelope.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1676.48,
      "end": 1679.04,
      "text": "Spade counted the bills and was putting them in his pocket",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1679.22,
      "end": 1681.9,
      "text": "when Brigid O'Shaughnessy came in carrying a tray."
    },
    {
      "start": 1682.76,
      "end": 1684.16,
      "text": "The boy would not eat.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1684.896,
      "end": 1686.16,
      "text": "Kyra took a cup of coffee.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1686.88,
      "end": 1687.26,
      "text": "The girl,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1687.34,
      "end": 1687.66,
      "text": "Gutman,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1687.76,
      "end": 1690.54,
      "text": "and Spade ate the scrambled eggs and bacon and toast"
    },
    {
      "start": 1690.8,
      "end": 1692.0,
      "text": "and marmalade she had prepared,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1692.18,
      "end": 1694.28,
      "text": "and drank two cups of coffee apiece."
    },
    {
      "start": 1695.44,
      "end": 1698.16,
      "text": "Then they settled down to wait the rest of the night through.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1700.032,
      "end": 1704.12,
      "text": "Gutman smoked a cigar and read Celebrated Criminal Cases of America,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1704.66,
      "end": 1707.48,
      "text": "now and then chuckling over or commenting on the"
    },
    {
      "start": 1707.48,
      "end": 1709.6,
      "text": "parts of its contents that he found interesting."
    },
    {
      "start": 1710.848,
      "end": 1714.16,
      "text": "Cairo nursed his bruised mouth and sulked on his end of the sofa.",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}